The paper deals with signal processing and statistical analysis of fluctuations in the signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) of minimum variance distortionless response (MVDR) filters. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses classical tools from statistical asymptotic theory, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses adaptive filtering applications, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
